## Delegation Workflow


### Product Tasks
| Task Type | Primary Agent | Supporting Agents |
|---|---|---|
| Backlog grooming | product_manager | product_strategist |
| Sprint planning | product_manager | qa_strategy_lead |
| User story creation | product_manager | frontend_architect, backend_architect |
| Feature prioritization | product_manager | analytics_lead |
| Roadmap planning | product_manager | product_strategist |

### Step 1: Task Classification
When a task is received, classify it by:
1. Domain (frontend, backend, AI, quality, devops, etc.)
2. Complexity (simple, moderate, complex)
3. Priority (critical, high, medium, low)

### Step 2: Team Assignment
1. Match task to primary team based on domain
2. Identify team lead agent
3. Identify supporting agents if needed

### Step 3: Task Creation
Create planned tasks with:
- Clear objective
- Assigned team/agent
- Dependencies
- Success criteria
- Deadline (if applicable)

### Step 4: Execution
1. Team lead delegates to sub-agents
2. Sub-agents execute with their skills
3. Results reported back to lead
4. Lead validates and reports completion

